message.content:
Breakfast
1. Oatmeal with fruit and nuts - add chopped up apple, blueberries, and walnuts for a tasty and filling start to the day.
2. Smoothie - blend together 1/2 banana, 1/4 cup of milk or almond milk, 1 scoop of vanilla protein powder, 1/4 cup of frozen berries, and ice for a delicious and nutritious breakfast option.

Lunch
1. Salad - make a large salad with spinach, broccoli, carrots, and cucumbers topped with grilled chicken or tofu with balsamic vinaigrette dressing for a light and filling lunch.
2. Veggie burger - make or buy a veggie burger and serve on a whole wheat bun with lettuce, tomato, avocado, and hummus for a hearty and protein-packed meal.

Dinner
1. Chicken stir fry - saute chicken breast in olive oil with onion, garlic, mushrooms, peppers, zucchini, broccoli, and bell pepper with a touch of soy sauce for a delicious dinner.
2. Quinoa bowl - cook quinoa and add in black beans, corn, red peppers, avocado, tomatoes, and salsa for a filling and fiber-filled meal.

Snacks
1. Fruit - have a handful of blueberries or an apple as a snack to keep you full and energized throughout the day.
2. Nuts/seeds - almonds, pumpkin seeds, or walnuts are great for a healthy and filling snack that will help curb your cravings without adding too many calories.
